---
/**
 * Guided walk — Chapter 3 of 6: "How big is it — and what won't they tell you?"
 * The air permit is the one record that fixes the plant's scale; it also locks
 * the load-bearing number behind a trade-secret redaction. Uses the Record
 * Teardown's `annotated` layout to show the CBI redaction directly.
 */
import Base from "../../../../../layouts/Base.astro";
import PathWayfinding from "../../../../../components/PathWayfinding.astro";
import RecordTeardown from "../../../../../components/RecordTeardown.astro";
import { AIR_TEARDOWN } from "../../../../../lib/teardowns";
import { chapterByStep, WALK_INDEX_HREF, WALK_TOTAL, walkHref } from "../../../../../lib/walk";
import { withBase } from "../../../../../lib/site";

const STEP = 3;
const prev = chapterByStep(STEP - 1);
const next = chapterByStep(STEP + 1);
---

<Base
  title="How big is it — Chapter 2"
  section="story"
  description="The air permit is the one record that fixes the data center's scale — and it locks the number that matters most behind a trade-secret redaction."
>
  <div class="walk-chapter-page">
    <PathWayfinding step={STEP} />

    <div class="walk-chapter-eyebrow">Chapter {STEP} of {WALK_TOTAL} · the guided walk</div>
    <h1 class="walk-chapter-h1">How big is it — and what won't they tell you?</h1>

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        Most of this project is described in documents the developer wrote, and
        most of those are vague about scale. The air permit is different: to set
        federally enforceable pollution limits, Ohio EPA had to count the plant's
        equipment, unit by unit. Read it for the <em>shape</em> it's forced to
        disclose — and notice where it stops.
      </p>
    </div>

    <RecordTeardown record={AIR_TEARDOWN} layout="annotated" />

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        The structure is unambiguous: three matched groups of generators and
        cooling towers — three data halls. The pollution caps are printed in black
        and white. But the single number that would convert “115 generators” into
        megawatts — the per-engine nameplate power — is withheld as a trade secret,
        so the widely-quoted <strong>~313 MW</strong> traces only to the draft
        public notice, not the issued permit. Knowing which is which is the skill.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout walk-takeaway">
      <p class="callout-title">What you can read anywhere now</p>
      <p>
        A <strong>synthetic-minor</strong> permit caps emissions just under the
        threshold that would trigger major-source review — so the caps tell you the
        operator's own ceiling. Repeated equipment groups reveal layout the plans
        won't. And a <strong>CBI / trade-secret redaction</strong> is not a dead end:
        it marks exactly which fact someone paid to keep out of the record.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="walk-explore-h">Explore this in the library</h2>
    <div class="doors">
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/site/records/")}>
        <span class="door-label">The permit record</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">The full extraction — emission units, caps, and the redaction note.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/timeline")}>
        <span class="door-label">Timeline</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">The draft, the comment period, and the final issuance, in sequence.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/docs/bigger-picture")}>
        <span class="door-label">The bigger picture</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">How the disclosed plant implies the compute — and the cooling load.</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <nav class="walk-nav" aria-label="Chapter navigation">
      {
        prev?.live ? (
          <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-prev" href={walkHref(prev.slug)}>← {prev.step}. {prev.title}</a>
        ) : prev ? (
          <span class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-prev is-disabled" title="Drafting">← {prev.step}. {prev.title}</span>
        ) : (
          <span></span>
        )
      }
      <a class="walk-nav-leave" href={WALK_INDEX_HREF}>All chapters</a>
      {
        next?.live ? (
          <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-next" href={walkHref(next.slug)}>{next.step}. {next.title} →</a>
        ) : next ? (
          <span class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-next is-disabled" title="Drafting">{next.step}. {next.title} →</span>
        ) : (
          <span></span>
        )
      }
    </nav>
  </div>
</Base>
